5.8. Calculator Record

  


Requirements

Overview: The Calculator record is the purpose for this solution. A Dealer will use this to calculate the delivery price of a furniture order. This record will always only be editable. Multiple Dealers can open their own version of the Calculator at the same time.

  


Accessed via: 

  * Main Menu | Calculator | Calculator



  


Sections and Fields: 

  * Tru-Haul logo at the top of the detail screen
  * Tru-Haul address: 



3270 Lower Valley Rd. 

Parkesburg, PA 19365 

  * Email Tru-Haul (link; opens the email client with the To: address auto-filled from the "Email Tru-Haul" setting; used by the Dealer to directly email Tru-Haul)
  * Dealer (the name of the Dealer for whom the calculations are being done; with the following special behaviors:
    * For Dealers: auto-set and read-only; displays the Contact name for the logged-in Dealer;
    * For Administrators: drop-list of all Dealer names; filters down as you type; defaults to blank)
  * Zip Code (number field; validate against unsupported zip codes; error on entry if the zip code is not supported: "The entered zip code is not supported. Please enter a supported zip code.")
  * City (read-only; displays the City associated with the Zip Code)
  * State (read-only; displays the State associated with the Zip Code)
  * Zone (read-only; hidden from Dealers; displays the Zone ID and Name, based on the selected "Zip Code")
  * Route Name (read-only; displays the "Route Name" for the associated "Zip Code" / "Zone")
  * Route Notes (read-only; visible if any "Route Notes" are specified for the displayed Route; displays the corresponding Route Notes)
  * Furniture (visible if "Dealer" and "Zip Code" are both set; embedded spreadsheet with one row per Furniture Type automatically included, with the following: 
    * Columns: 
      * Furniture Type (auto-set and read-only)
      * Furniture Value (required; number field to 2 decimals) 
      * Curbside Dropoff (auto-set and read-only; number field to 2 decimals, rounding to the nearest whole dollar, which still displaying the ".00" at the end; with the following behaviors: 
        * if the selected Furniture Type has the "White Glove Delivery Only" checkbox not checked: displays the Curbside Dropoff price for the row)
        * if the selected Furniture Type has the "White Glove Delivery Only" checkbox checked: displays "N/A") 
      * White Glove (auto-set and read-only; number field to 2 decimals, rounding to the nearest whole dollar, which still displaying the ".00" at the end; displays the White Glove Delivery price for the row) 
    * Automatically sorted by: The "Sort Order" of the Furniture Types 
    * Buttons to insert/append/remove rows: N/A (none) 
    * Show 10 rows without scrolling) 
    * Notes:
      * If values are filled in for multiple furniture types, the cost for each type will go down since the delivery cost is shared by the various types (see Pricing Calculations)



  


  * Curbside Dropoff<*>: $ (auto-set and read-only; number field to 2 decimals, rounding to the nearest whole dollar, while still displaying the ".00" at the end; with the following behaviors: 
    * visible if there is a Dealer and valid Zip Code specified and there is at least one row of the Furniture spreadsheet that contains an "Amount" value for a Furniture Type with the "White Glove Delivery Only" checkbox not checked; 
    * note that the label includes the conditionally-visible asterisk ("*") if there is an "Amount" value for at least one row of each ("White Glove Delivery Only" checkbox checked and not checked); 
    * displays the total price based on the Zip Code, Furniture Value, and Furniture Type, see Calculations) 
  * White Glove Delivery: $ (auto-set and read-only; number field to 2 decimals, rounding to the nearest whole dollar, which still displaying the ".00" at the end; visible if valid zip code and dealer specified; displays the total price based on the Zip Code, Furniture Value, and Furniture Type, see Calculations) 
  * Totals clarification message: "*The curbside dropoff total includes the white glove delivery price for furniture not eligible for curbside dropoff." (message in gray italics; visible if the "Curbside Dropoff $" field is visible and there is at least one row with an "Amount" value for a Furniture Type that has the "White Glove Delivery Only" checkbox checked)
  * Missing Fields warning (bold green read-only messages visible in place of the two totals:
    * if Zip Code is not specified: "Please specify a zip code."; 
    * if Zip Code is specified but Dealer is not specified (and visible only for Admin users, since the Dealer is auto-set and read-only for Dealers): "Please select a Dealer.")
  * Email this Quote (visible if Dealer and Zip Code are set; link to send an email; opens a new tab with the following: 
    * Email address (editable; plain text field; defaults to email address for the selected Dealer)
    * Continue (button; sends the breakdown and total from the calculator to the selected email address; see the Quote Email section of the proposal)
  * Print this Quote (link; visible if Dealer and Zip Code are set; generates the Quote Printout PDF and opens it in a new tab)



  


  


Data Access: 

  * The calculator will be specific to each dealer
  * Employees & Support are able to run the Calculator for any dealer



  


Special Considerations: 

  * Copy Record: N/A
  * Delete Record: N/A
  * Merge Record: N/A



  


Other Notes:

  * When a Dealer logs into the system, they will be logged directly into the calculator.
  * When leaving the Calculator or closing the tab, the browser will prompt to make sure that you want to leave.

Jonathan Bergen 04/25/2024: To look up the price for a zone + bucket:

Assign Parameter vPrice = NA;

Assign Parameter vDeliveryType = ""

Assign vBottomBucketNum = 1;

Assign vTopBucketNum = CountListItems( Buckets);

Assign vPriceBucket = ListNum( Buckets, RoundUpToTheNearestBucketValue( vPrice));

Assign vBottomBucketMarkup = ZoneField( CalculatorZone, MinBucketMarkup);

Assign vTopBucketMarkup = ZoneFiled( CalculatorZone, MaxBucketMarkup);

  


Assign vZoneMarkup = ((vBottomBucketNum - vPriceBucket) * vBottomBucketMarkup + Abs(vTopBucketNum - vPriceBucket) * vTopBucketMarkup ) / ((vBottomBucketNum - vPriceBucket) + Abs(vTopBucketNum - vPriceBucket);

BasePriceSheetField( vPriceBucket, vDeliveryTypeFee * vZoneMarkup)
